
# commit 457084cc48c99b6f534a00dd994ffcbeb71200c3
# Author: Jambunathan K <kjambunathan@gmail.com>
# Date:   Sun Jan 19 17:09:05 2020 +0530

    Update build files to generate and upload ODT user manuals

    * .gitignore: Ignore HTML and PDF files only in the `doc/' subdir.
    Those in the `docs/' subdir are version-controlled and served via
    https://kjambunathan.github.io/org-mode-ox-odt/.

    * doc/Makefile (%.html): Use variable `TEXI2HTMLEXTRA'
    (org-odt.html): Set `TEXI2HTMLEXTRA' so that the HTML manual is
    split at chapters, and output to `org-odt-manual/' subdir.
    (clean): Remove subdir `ord-odt-manual'.
    (html, pdf): Don't build `org-odt-old.html' and
    `org-odt-old.pdf'.

    * mk/default.mk (TEXI2HTMLEXTRA): New variable.  Use this to pass
    additional command options to ${TEXI2HTML}.  The default value
    builds a monolithic HTML manual with numbered sections.

    * mk/odtpkg.mk (DOCROOT): Root directory for Github page served
    via https://kjambunathan.github.io/org-mode-ox-odt/.  Set to
    `docs/' subdir.
    (odtmanual): New target to upload the ODT user manual to $(DOCROOT).

    See #64.


